ÜgÂ]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1110";s:4:"name";s:20:"Diabetic Nephropathy";s:4:"slug";s:20:"diabetic-nephropathy";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1110";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4681:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">A simple explanation of the ailment would be nerve damage from diabetes is called diabetic neuropathy. Neuropathy (or diffuse neuropathy) is a nerve disorder which may be categorized as sensory neuropathy, motor neuropathy or autonomic neuropathy. Neuropathy can be caused by both Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes.Â </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When your blood sugar levels are too high, it can damage the covering on your nerves or the blood vessels that bring oxygen to your nerves. These damaged nerves may stop sending messages or may send messages slowly or at the wrong times.</span>

<b>Causes: </b><b>
</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Incidences are more common in patients with poor control, overweight, have higher levels of blood fat and blood pressure, and are over the age of 40. The risk of developing neuropathies is relative to the personâ€™s diabetic history.</span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Smoking</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Consuming AlcoholÂ </span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Chronic Liver or Kidney Disease</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Vitamin B deficiency</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">High Blood Sugar</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genes</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Symptoms:</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The common symptoms for diabetic neuropathy are:Â </span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Numbness in the hands or feet, often on both sides</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain in the hands, feet, or legs</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Foot problems, such as calluses, dry skin, cracked skin, claw toes, and ankle weakness</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Neuropathy can also cause problems with other parts of your body. While it harms your digestive tract, heart, sex organs, or eyes. This can lead to symptoms such as</span>

&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Indigestion</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Diarrhea or Constipation</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Dizziness, especially when standing up</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bladder Infections</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Erectile Dysfunction</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Vaginal Dryness</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weakness</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Weight Loss</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Depression and Insomnia</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Loss in Eyesight</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Excessive Sweating</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Foods to Eat:Â </b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A healthy diet is always recommended for managing your blood sugar and diabetes complications such as diabetic neuropathy. One should focus on a healthy eating plan that's naturally rich in nutrients and low in fat and calories, such as:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Vegetables, fruits, legumes and whole grains</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fat-free and low-fat dairy products</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Lean meats, fish, and poultry without the skin</span></li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

<b>Treatment</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A range of these parallel therapies may help lessen neuropathy pain, improve blood flow, and reduce the chances of muscle wasting. These include massage, physical therapy, acupuncture, and chiropractic therapy. However, these methods are unlikely to provide long-term solutions. The best practice would be to manage blood sugar levels through medication and lifestyle changes.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">While it is currently not possible to reverse diabetic neuropathy, people can take steps to reduce the risk of severe symptoms and further complications.</span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}